"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 22, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fgk1665703264194.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fgk1665703264194.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fgk1665703264194.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fgk1665703264194\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies the character set supported by the current Uniface installation.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"fgk1665703264194__topic_d145985e1_d145986e1_d145987e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgk1665703264194__p_d145988e1_d145989e1_d145990e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">NLS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">LanguageCode</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fgk1665703264194__section_wh1_fsg_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1028999e65\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">LanguageCode</var>—character set abbreviation</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">NLS language codes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">Abbreviation</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Character set name</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">USA</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">English </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">CEN</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Central European</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">CYR</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Cyrillic</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">ARB</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Arabic</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">ELL</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Greek</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">HEB</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Hebrew</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">CHZ</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Simplified Chinese</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">KOR</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Korean</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">JPN</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Japanese</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__1\">CHT</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17819e1_d17820e1_d17821e1__entry__2\">Traditional Chinese</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"fgk1665703264194__table_d17822e1_d17823e1_d17824e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Character set selected during Uniface\n                installation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">File section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rpa1665702674458.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rpa1665702674458.html\" title=\"The [uniface_dlls] section of the initialization file specifies the DLLs used by Uniface.\">[uniface_dlls]</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fgk1665703264194__section_zbq_psg_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1028999e232\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The Uniface installation program initializes the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">NLS</span> setting to the\n        abbreviation of the character set selected during Uniface installation (in the Character set\n        selection screen). For example, if the selected character set is Japanese, then\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">NLS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=JPN</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Although you can modify this setting, it is recommended that you keep the installed value.\n        Furthermore, the installed character set should be the same as the language version of your\n        Microsoft Windows installation. For example, when you install Uniface on a Japanese Windows\n        system, select the Japanese character set.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">If you modify this setting, make sure that the Windows installation supports your chosen\n        character set and that the corresponding <span class=\"ph filepath\">.dll</span> file exists in Uniface's\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">/bin</span> directory. For Arabic, Hebrew, Simplified Chinese, Korean, and\n        Japanese, the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.dll</span> files are installed in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/bin</span>\n        directory and are named <span class=\"ph filepath\">unls<var class=\"keyword varname\">LAN</var>.dll</span>, where\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">LanguageCode</var> is the language abbreviation. If the\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">.dll</span> file does not exist, or if Microsoft Windows does not support\n        the character set, Uniface uses <code class=\"ph codeph\">NLS=USA</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">NLS</code> setting can be taken from either the local or the default\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527488\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527488\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "NLS Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 22, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifies the character set supported by the current Uniface installation. NLS = LanguageCode Arguments LanguageCode —character set abbreviation Table 1. NLS language codes Abbreviation Character set name USA English CEN Central European CYR Cyrillic ARB Arabic ELL Greek HEB Hebrew CHZ Simplified Chinese KOR Korean JPN Japanese CHT Traditional Chinese Default value Character set selected during Uniface installation File section [uniface_dlls] Description The Uniface installation program initializes the NLS setting to the abbreviation of the character set selected during Uniface installation (in the Character set selection screen). For example, if the selected character set is Japanese, then NLS =JPN . Although you can modify this setting, it is recommended that you keep the installed value. Furthermore, the installed character set should be the same as the language version of your Microsoft Windows installation. For example, when you install Uniface on a Japanese Windows system, select the Japanese character set. If you modify this setting, make sure that the Windows installation supports your chosen character set and that the corresponding .dll file exists in Uniface's /bin directory. For Arabic, Hebrew, Simplified Chinese, Korean, and Japanese, the .dll files are installed in the /bin directory and are named unls LAN .dll , where LanguageCode is the language abbreviation. If the .dll file does not exist, or if Microsoft Windows does not support the character set, Uniface uses NLS=USA . The NLS setting can be taken from either the local or the default .ini file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}